latestPosts.caption:
The haldi that turned into a crazy Holi! From the sweetest surprise performance by both the moms and Niyati’s girl squad (cue the cutest reactions!) to a haldi celebration like no other—this was pure madness. 

When Konark told us on day one that he was planning this, we knew this couple was all about fun. And they truly set the mood for the next three days—mad, crazy, carefree, and an absolute blast! As Konark said, “Capture us like you’re capturing two best friends.” That’s exactly what we did. 

Before the haldi ceremony could even wrap up, the colours came out, and the Holi madness began! Our cameras got a full blast too, but shoutout to the amazing folks at NPS Nikon for getting all our gear serviced just in time for the evening cocktail. What a (colourful) blast, quite liberally! Pun intended.

latestPosts.caption:
What an incredible time we had with Niyati and Konark over the past few days! They are THE most fun bride and groom you will ever come across and the sweetest people too. This is how weddings should be raw, real, emotional and quirky! I mean ever heard of sindoor in the after party on the dance floor? (That’s a photo for another time). From the laughter to the tears, every moment was so genuine, authentic unscripted, and real—exactly what we love capturing as photographers. Both the families, the Kanakias and the Gowarikars are truly the best folks to hang around with! And that’s exactly what we did past three days, chilled on the dance floor with the most amazing couple! We congratulate them at pulling off ‘The Kon of the century!’ And yes getting married ✨✨✨
